You may want to try compiling the newer rtNEAT release instead of=
 
the original one:

http://nn.cs.utexas.edu/keyword?rtneat

Note that the =
rtNEAT source package has a lot of the extra stuff 
like guile and gtkmm st=
ripped out, making it easier to compile.  
Even though it includes rtNEAT, =
it also includes the complete code 
for regular generational NEAT, and in f=
act even that code has some 
updates making it more recent than the origina=
l NEAT code.

If you still have problems please let me know.

ken
